The paper proposes a method for interpreting and understanding graph convolutional neural networks (GCNs), which are commonly used in fields such as scene semantic relationship analysis, natural language processing, and few-shot learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
